      • toMapPixelsProjected

        public static android.graphics.PointF toMapPixelsProjected(double latitude,
                                           double longitude,
                                           android.graphics.PointF reuse)
        Performs only the first computationally heavy part of the projection. Call toMapPixelsTranslated to get the final position.
        Parameters:
        latitude - the latitude of the point
        longitude - the longitude of the point
        reuse - just pass null if you do not have a Point to be 'recycled'.
        Returns:
        intermediate value to be stored and passed to toMapPixelsTranslated.

      • toMapPixelsTranslated

        public android.graphics.PointF toMapPixelsTranslated(android.graphics.PointF in,
                                            android.graphics.PointF reuse)
        Performs the second computationally light part of the projection. Returns results in screen coordinates.
        Parameters:
        in - the Point calculated by the toMapPixelsProjected
        reuse - just pass null if you do not have a Point to be 'recycled'.
        Returns:
        the Point containing the Screen coordinates of the initial LatLng passed to the toMapPixelsProjected.

      • latLongToPixelXY

        public static android.graphics.PointF latLongToPixelXY(double latitude,
                                       double longitude,
                                       float levelOfDetail,
                                       android.graphics.PointF reuse)
        Converts a point from latitude/longitude WGS-84 coordinates (in degrees) into pixel XY coordinates at a specified level of detail.
        Parameters:
        latitude - Latitude of the point, in degrees
        longitude - Longitude of the point, in degrees
        levelOfDetail - Level of detail, from 1 (lowest detail) to 23 (highest detail)
        reuse - An optional Point to be recycled, or null to create a new one automatically
        Returns:
        Output parameter receiving the X and Y coordinates in pixels
